The paper deals with signal reconstruction from compressed sensing measurements, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The use of weighted $\ell_1$ minimization is a machine learning technique (cs.LG) that is commonly used in compressed sensing. The paper also discusses stability and robustness guarantees, which are topics in numerical analysis (cs.NA) and statistical inference (cs.SI).
